A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend an Act to provide for a homestead exemption from City of Peachtree City ad
2 valorem taxes for municipal purposes in the amount of $5,000.00 of the assessed value of the
3 homestead for residents of that city who are 65 years of age or over and whose income does
4 not exceed $30,000.00, approved May 5, 2005 (Ga. L. 2005, p. 3719), so as to increase the
5 income cap related to qualifying for such exemption to $60,000.00; to increase the value of
6 the exemption to $30,000.00 of the assessed value; to provide for compliance with
7 constitutional requirements; to provide for a referendum, effective dates, and automatic
8 repeal; to provide for mandatory execution of election and judicial remedies regarding failure
9 to comply; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
11 SECTION 1.
12 An Act to provide for a homestead exemption from City of Peachtree City ad valorem taxes
13 for municipal purposes in the amount of $5,000.00 of the assessed value of the homestead
14 for residents of that city who are 65 years of age or over and whose income does not exceed
15 $30,000.00, approved May 5, 2005 (Ga. L. 2005, p. 3719), is amended by revising
16 subsection (b) of Section 1 as follows:
H. B. 703
- 1 -

25 LC 47 3442/AP
17 "(b) Each resident of the City of Peachtree City who is a senior citizen is granted an
18 exemption on that person's homestead from City of Peachtree City ad valorem taxes for
19 municipal purposes in the amount of $30,000.00 of the assessed value of that homestead.
20 The exemption granted by this subsection shall only be granted if that person's income
21 together with the income of the spouse who also occupies and resides at such homestead
22 does not exceed $60,000.00 for the immediately preceding year. The value of that property
23 in excess of such exempted amount shall remain subject to taxation."
24 SECTION 2.
25 In accordance with the requirements of Article VII, Section II of the Constitution of the State
26 of Georgia, this Act shall not become law unless it receives the requisite two-thirds' majority
27 vote in both the Senate and the House of Representatives.
28 SECTION 3.
29 The municipal election superintendent of the City of Peachtree City shall call and conduct
30 an election as provided in this section for the purpose of submitting this Act to the electors
31 of the City of Peachtree City for approval or rejection. The election superintendent shall
32 conduct that election on the Tuesday following the first Monday in November, 2025, and
33 shall issue the call and conduct such election as provided by general law. The election
34 superintendent shall cause the date and purpose of the election to be published once a week
35 for two weeks immediately preceding the date thereof in the official organ of Fayette County.
36 The ballot shall have written or printed thereon the words:
